> The kernel is never
> > > "swapped out".  So if you are in kernel mode,
> going into do_page_fault
> > > in arch/i386/mm/fault.c there is no path to swap
> a page in.
> > 
> > Actually there is - when the page fault was caused
> by *_user. 
> 
